  "text": "In HAR literature, it is challenging to distinguish between static activities, such as lying, standing, and sitting, since the human body only has slight acceleration in these activities. This problem was addressed in [CITATION_1] by classifying the activity as static or dynamic, and then considering specific features for the static activities. In this work, we let the proposed deep learning model implicitly distinguish between the static activities without adding any new classifier. In Figure 7 , we show how the proposed method improved the performance of static activities significantly as well as a slight improvement in the performance of the dynamic activities. More precisely, the performance increased by 5% and 1% for static and dynamic activities, respectively. Position-independent [CITATION_2] position-aware [CITATION_3] Position-independent (This work)",
